						               													<description>A tabletop space combat game played with customizable spaceship models called RIGs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Guild of RIG Pilots has openings for new members and has posted a challenge to all pilots with a RIG. Pilots are to battle each other in order to earn a place in their ranks. You are one of these pilots!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Pilots battle it out by drawing from constructed decks and playing cards to activate System Discs (SD). Activated SDs can have various types of weapon and special abilities. These are then physically launched from your RIG. &amp;#10;- Five different RIGs (buildable spaceship models) can be customized by mounting the parts the way players want and the ships can also be mixed to build a totally new RIG.&amp;#10;- Configure your RIG by installing various types of Platforms into your RIG's Modules and construct your deck according to the installed Platform Systems.&amp;#10;- Earn points during battle to eventually be accepted into the Guild. As you earn Battle Points, you'll gain benefits in the Battlespace to aid you on your way to Victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Victory conditions: &amp;#10;The game ends when a player's RIG is destroyed or after the turn where a player's deck runs out. &amp;#10;- The player with the surviving RIG wins the game.&amp;#10;- If both players survived when the game ends, the player with the most armor wins the game.&amp;#10;- If the armor amounts are equal when the game ends, the Junior Guild Member wins the game.&amp;#10;- If both players are Junior Guild Members when the game ends, the players must place their RIGs 2 Proximity card lengths apart and load 1 SD each. The players launch simultaneously. The player who achieves the closest Proximity wins the game. A Direct or Surface Hit is an automatic loss. Relaunch if both players scored a Direct or Surface Hit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;Neal @ CGT&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
